content.description: Stand start on the right side.  Feels a bit forced, but worthwhile if you're already there.
content.location: The next boulder east of the Minotaur (V5)

content.description: Stand start on the left side and move up and right.  The sit start variation is fun and adds a little difficulty.
content.location: The next boulder east of the Minotaur (V5)

content.description: Cruxs would have to be 3rd and 4th move then keeping balance at the top.
content.protection: Two pads. Maybe a buddy to catch.
content.location: Just past underworld over the rock pile, take a right. It kinda cuts back away from the labyrinth, across another small rock pile. Stay left when on the rock pile, then about 30 yards boulder will be on the left. Opens up on top of flattish bigger rock pile. You can see Columbia's biggest boulder from here G?.

content.description: A cool jug haul on the west side of The Underworld Cave.  Start back in the cave on a large incut jug.  Climb up and to the right.
content.location: When you see the Micah Miller Wall, turn right and scramble over some small boulders.  The problem is on the West side of The Underworld Cave.  Sits beside Pope Problem 426 (V1).

content.description: A 35 foot traverse, great for beginners or ARC training.  Start far left on the main large wall that Minotaur (V5) is on.  Traverse over to the starting holds for Minotaur.
content.location: Same wall that the Minotaur is on in the center of the Labyrinth Main.

content.description: Sandbagged. Climb up the arete to the tooth and traverse left.
content.location: In front of Pope's Prow. If your facing Pope's Prow turn around and it's right there.

content.description: Sit start with a slope and a crimp.  Climb up and slightly right.  This is also the downclimb, so make sure your pads are stacked accordingly.
content.location: 25 yards behind (north of) The Scoop/The Minotaur

content.description: Stand or sit start and stem your way up. Sit start in the crack is a V5. Stretch your back before attempting this party trick!
Sit start on the jug and climb the arete
content.location: Once you see the Micah Miller Wall, turn right and scramble over some small boulders.  The boulder sits on the west side of The Underworld Cave.

content.description: Stand start and climb up and right to the giant horns.
content.location: In the center of the Labyrinth Main

content.description: Sit start on two opposing fins and climb straight up.  V1 stand start.
content.location: The Micha Miller Wall will be the first area you see upon entering the labyrinth main from the state park.  This problem is on the rightmost side of that wall.

content.description: Sit start and climb directly up the prow.
content.location: When you see The Micah Miller Wall, turn right and scramble over some small boulders. The routes lay on the west side of The Underworld Cave.

content.description:
Sit start as far down as you can with a left on the slanted shelf and a right around the arete.  Make a big move up to the large jug and mantle out.

Note:  I'm not sure if this is a variation to the route "Little Bulge Left" or the original route.  Let me know and I can change it up.
content.location: When you see The Micah Miller Wall, turn right and scramble over some small boulders.  The routes lay on the west side of The Underworld Cave.

content.description:
Start low (sit start for tall people) with a high right crimp and a low left hand around the arete.  Hug the prow and work your way up to the point, mantling out left.

I'm sure this route has been done before.  If anyone knows FA info or the actual route name, let me know and I'll change it.  There is likely another sit start variation to the right, too.  Maybe V4 or better...
Start low matched on the undercling/sidepull. Climb the left arete.

Start matched on under-clings from ground level of the cave. Climb out on positive features, working your way to a jug rail. Set up for a big move (the crux) into a good letter opener slot in the crack (This move can be spanned by taller climbers, but will require more difficult beta for shorter climbers, thus the slash grade of V7/V9). Fun climbing and super classic.
content.location:
If referencing the guide book, located in The Labyrinth West. From the horse trail, take the

second

path to the right. At the fork, veer left, following this past the cave route on your right hand side. Keep following this trail through boulders. Eventually, take the trail, which is the second right at the fork. Follow this pathway all the way up and along the ridge-line. The Aries boulder is on The Underworld Cave, just south of the Micha Miller Wall.

content.description: Start low on the left facing flake.  Move up and left to the arete just off the ground.  It does not top out.
content.location: 25 yards behind (north of) The Scoop (V4) or the Minotaur (V5)
